LAC Minerals Ltd said it will suspendunderground mining and exploration at its Lake Shore Mine atKirkland Lake, Ontario, on April 30, pending results of asurface exploration drilling program.    LAC said it does not expect the decision to affectearnings, but 44 employees will be affected.    The company said it has completed mining the crown pillarwhich has produced 71,000 ounces of gold since 1983. In 1986,the mine produced 10,600 ounces. LAC said it will continuesurface drilling in 1987 to determine if further undergroundexploration work is warranted.    Reuter&#3;